# UI Patterns

## Material 3

Use Material 3 (`useMaterial3: true` in `ThemeData`). Dark theme is the
default. Light theme is optional and user-toggled.

## Shared Widgets

All reusable UI components must live in `lib/shared/widgets/`. Do not duplicate
widget logic across features — extract into shared widgets.

## Required State Widgets

Every list screen and data-loading screen must handle all three states:

| State | Widget to use |
|---|---|
| Loading | `LoadingShimmer` (`shared/widgets/loading_shimmer.dart`) |
| Error | `ErrorView` (`shared/widgets/error_view.dart`) — message + retry button |
| Empty list | `EmptyState` (`shared/widgets/empty_state.dart`) — icon + message |

Never show a blank screen during loading. Never show a raw exception string to
the user. Always provide a retry action on error screens.

## Optimistic UI Rules

Optimistic UI (updating the displayed state before the server confirms the
action) is **only** allowed for non-destructive reads.

**Never** use optimistic UI for power actions:
- Start VM / container
- Stop VM / container
- Force Stop VM / container
- Reboot VM / container
- Backup trigger

Power actions must reflect actual server state after the Proxmox task completes.
Always poll task status and update the UI only when the task status is `ok` or
`error`.

## Localization

All user-visible strings must be defined as keys in `lib/l10n/app_en.arb` and
accessed via the generated `AppLocalizations` class. **Never** hard-code display
strings in widgets.

```dart
// Correct
Text(AppLocalizations.of(context)!.vmStatusRunning)

// Wrong — hard-coded string in widget
Text('Running')
```

UI labels must follow Proxmox VE terminology for consistency with the Proxmox
web UI: Node, Virtual Machine, Container, Storage, Task, Backup, etc.
